如中国向美国出口原料药持续受影响，几个月内美国药店将空空如也。
If Chinese exports of APIs to the United States continue to be affected, US pharmacies will be empty within a few months.
金淼。
Miao Jin.
界面新闻                      。
Interface news.
界面新闻。
Interface news.
界面新闻是中国具有影响力的原创财经新媒体，只服务于独立思考的人群。
Interface News is an original and influential new financial media in China, serving only the people who think independently.
记者：金淼  编辑：许悦“ 中国、印度两个原料药大国相继受到疫情影响，引发了全球的恐慌。
Reporter: Xu Miao: "China, India two major API countries have been affected by the epidemic, causing global panic.
”中国和印度对制药行业至关重要——2019年，这两个国家供应了全球所需原料药总量的60%。
China and India are crucial to the pharmaceutical industry - supplying 60 per cent of the total global API requirement in 2019.
在中国和印度相继陷入新冠疫情危机后，全球制药产业也迎来动荡。
The global pharmaceutical industry is also in turmoil as China and India fall into a new crown crisis.
3月15日，福克斯新闻在周末论坛上邀请了美国国会议员Earl L.Buddy Carter讨论了新冠肺炎是如何影响美国药品供应的。
On March 15, Fox News invited U. S. Congressman Earl L. Buddy Carter to a weekend forum to discuss how pneumonia in the United States affects access to medicines.
Earl L.Buddy Carter在采访中表示，由于将药品生产外包给了中国及印度，因此美国的制药业依赖于中国及印度。
Earl L. Buddy Carter said in an interview that the U. S. pharmaceutical industry is dependent on China and India for outsourcing drug production to China and India.
美国黑斯廷斯中心高级顾问Rosemary Gibson也持有类似的观点，如果中国停止向美国出口药品生产的核心成分，几个月内，美国药店的货架就会空空如也。
Rosemary Gibson, a senior adviser at the Hastings Center, takes a similar view, saying that if China stopped exporting the core components of drug production to the US, shelves at US pharmacies would be empty in a matter of months.
二者都主张美国应有属于自己独立的制药产业链。
Both argue that the US should have its own independent pharmaceutical industry chain.
同时Earl L.Buddy Carter在采访中透露，为了达到激励药企返回美国本土的目的，国会议员办公室正在制定相关法律，鼓励企业将工厂迁回美国。
Meanwhile, Earl L. Buddy Carter said in an interview that Congress is working on legislation to encourage companies to move their factories back to the United States in order to encourage them to return home.
Earl L.Buddy Carter采访中表示，目前美国90%的抗生素、布洛芬、氢化可的松和维生素都来自于中国。
Earl L. Buddy Carter said in an interview that 90% of all antibiotics, ibuprofen, hydrocortisone and vitamins in the United States now come from China.
事实上自2月27日，FDA就已经表示，一种与新冠病毒相关的药品供应出现短缺，但一直未公布其具体品种。
In fact, since Feb. 27, the FDA has said there is a shortage of a new-crown-virus-related drug, but it hasn't disclosed its exact varieties.
美国食药监当天也表示，有药企通知存在成品制剂供应短缺的问题，其中20种药物供应链与中国密切相关。
The U. S. Food and Drug Administration also said the same day, pharmaceutical companies notified that there is a shortage of finished products, 20 of which are closely linked to China.
虽然目前国内尚未有关于原料药禁止出口的相关规定，但是作为另个原料药出口大国——印度，由于受原料药短缺影响已经于3月3日表示，当日起，对扑热息痛、替硝唑、红霉素、维生素B12、肝素、布洛芬等26种原料药和成品药限制出口。
Although there is no domestic ban on the export of APIs, India, another major API exporter, indicated on March 3 that it had restricted the export of 26 APIs and finished products, including paracetamol, tinidazole, erythromycin, vitamin B12, heparin and ibuprofen.
而该举措将会进一步加剧全球解热镇痛类原料的供应紧张。
The move would further strain the global supply of analgesic materials.
今年2月，印度工业联合会在接受印度国内采访时已经表示，手头的材料仅可供两到三个月生产。
In an interview in India in February, the Confederation of Indian Industry said the material at hand would only last two to three months.
事实上，自2月起，受疫情影响，国内的原料药价格已经开始出现上涨。
In fact, domestic API prices have begun to rise since February due to the epidemic.
以维生素为例，根据博亚和讯数据显示，近期多个维生素品种市场报价大涨，其中维生素B1、生物素、 维生素K3、维生素E、烟酰胺、维生素D3、维生素A等涨幅居前，2020 年 3 月 5 日报价分别为 325 元、325 元、92.5 元、 65 元、53 元、107.5 元、330 元每千克，较1 月 20 日分别上涨了 106%、86%、 59%、34%、18%、16%、7%。
Taking vitamins as an example, market prices for several vitamin varieties have surged recently, with vitamin B1, biotin, vitamin K3, vitamin E, nicotinamide, vitamin D3 and vitamin A leading the price rises on March 5, 2020, up 106 percent, 86 percent, 59 percent, 34 percent, 18 percent, 16 percent and 7 percent, respectively.
北京鼎臣医药管理咨询管理中心创始人史立臣在接受《21世纪经济报道》采访时表示，随着中国原料药企业的复工，供应会逐渐增加，但短时间内受运输、出口检疫、企业生产等影响，国外市场短缺药品恢复供应仍需一段时间。
In an interview with 21st Century Economic Report, founder of Beijing's Dingchen Medical and Consulting Management Center, Shi Licheng told the 21st Century Economic Report that, while the supply of Chinese APIs will gradually increase as they resume work, it will take some time before the shortages in foreign markets resume as a result of transportation, export quarantine and enterprise production.
但同时，史立臣也提到抗生素、维生素、氨基酸等大宗原料药的产业链迁出对于国内的环保及原料药产业链升级也将带来益处，“中国的原料药生产企业可以转向生产附加值较高的高端原料药。
At the same time, however, Slickson noted that the relocation of the bulk APIs, such as antibiotics, vitamins and amino acids, would also benefit the environmental protection and upgrading of the API industry chain in China, where "Chinese APIs manufacturers can switch to higher value added high-end APIs.
”未经授权 禁止转载。
